A case brought by hairdressers has been dismissed by the Western Cape High Court. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A case brought by hairdressers has been dismissed by the Western Cape High Court. The stylists wanted to be allowed to service customers under level 4, saying they were struggling to survive. SA lockdown: Restaurants plead with government to reopen The judge said the application was defective as it failed to cite the Cooperative Governance, Small Business and the Trade and Industry ministers as respondents. The applicants also failed to get the support of the Employers organisation for hairdressing, cosmetology and beauty technicians. No cost order was made. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.